{
  "stem": "18670.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 243.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I said to myself, it's going to cost me the stripes if I have a fight with him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 65,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I've worked hard enough to become a sergeant.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I took him to the commanding officer, who was Pennsylvania Dutch-- his name was Fluch, F-L-U-C-H-- and I filed a complaint.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And our commanding officer said, you know, Sergeant, he says, you're supposed to take orders.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He's superior, outranks you.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he wasn't entitled to do what he did.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I agreed with the officer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the end of the story is they took this guy-- he was an alcoholic on top of it-- they shipped them out.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 66,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So-- And while you were in this area, did you have any contact with Jews who were coming out of camps or Jews who were coming out of hiding in the Mainz area?",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When we march into Mainz, the sergeant that's marching with the infantry division, the group of Germans that greeted him, the first person to greet him was his own father, who had been in hiding.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was a college professor and he'd been in hiding in Mainz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yes, I had met some Jews that had been in hiding.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Unique thing was that some of those Jews, particularly one that became the police chief-- he was not Jewish but his wife was, and his son-- were hidden by big-shot Nazis whose family was all involved with the Gestapo, with the Air Force, and everything else.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And when I asked them, how come, did you know that you were losing the war, he said, when I joined the Nazi Party before Hitler came to power, he said, I felt that he was the messiah.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 67,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I found out soon enough he was not the messiah.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
